<title>UK: Lonrho sees JCI decision soon.</title>
<headline>Lonrho sees JCI decision soon.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Lonrho Plc said on Tuesday it expected to decide within the next few weeks whether to continue merger negotiations with South Africa's JCI Ltd.</p>
<p>&quot;The talks are still at a preliminary stage, but a decision will likely be reached within the next month whether to continue the talks,&quot; a Lonrho spokesman said.</p>
<p>He declined to be more specific. The Financial Times reported a decision could be reached within days.</p>
<p>JCI and Lonrho announced last month they were holding preliminary talks about a possible link-up.</p>
<p>A merger between the two would create a mining powerhouse with a market capitalisation over three billion dollars.</p>
